Russian forces struck a maternity hospital in Mariupol, Zelensky says
Before Vice President Harris landed in Poland on March 9, Russian forces struck a maternity hospital in Mariupol, causing massive damage. (Hadley Green, Drea Cornejo/The Washington Post)
By Paulina Firozi
,  
Karla Adam
